FBIS4-35392 "drnes105_j_94004" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Saudi Arabia King Fahd Undergoes Gallstone Surgery King Fahd Undergoes Gallstone Surgery LD3105201194 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Television Network in Arabic 1830 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105201194 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Television Network Arabic BFN [Excerpts] We have received the following from the Royal Court: The custodian of the two holy mosques, King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud, yesterday evening, 30 May, underwent a medical examination at the King Fahd Hospital for the Armed Forces in Jeddah. During the examination, a stone was discovered in the passage leading to the gall bladder. The stone was successfully removed with a surgical probe. [passage omitted] The king left the hospital this afternoon for al-Salam Palace in good health. [passage omitted]
